  <p>According to what Inegi figures, the construction industry was affected by an increase in commodities price,
   which amounted an increase of 15.32% YoY in 2021. At national level, the inputs of corrugated rod, iron and steel wire,
  and wire rod annually increased their prices by 32.79%, 24.37% and 44.07%, respectively.</p>

  <p>Regarding the loans granted by Infonavit, these amounted over 530 thousand during 2021, increasing by 11.6% compared
    to 2020 and 6.6% against the target set for 2021. Of the total, 61% were destined to the acquisition of new or existent
    housing, construction, and liabilities payment, while the remaining 39% were used for remodeling or improvement.</p>

  <p>Looking ahead to 2022, Infonavit, in line with its Annual Operative Program 2022, estimated that by the end
    of this year, a total of almost 596 thousand credits will be granted, both mortgage and non-mortgage, which
     would represent an increase of ~12% vs. 2021.</p>

